<br>
If you have the new UI you can use the pet control window to issue commands by clicking the mouse.<br>
<br>
For me, however, i made hotkeys ( started before this thing was implemented ) with the various commands.  I actually prefer this to the pet command window as it is faster.<br>
<br>
List:<br>
<br>
1.  /pet kill OR /pet attack - tells the pet to atack whatever you have targetted.  You will get a message saying: &quot;Jabober tells you 'I am attacking YOUR_TARGET Master'&quot;<br>
<br>
2.  /pet back off - backs the pet off of your target so it does not attack.  Not as useful early on, very useful later.<br>
<br>
3.  /pet guard me OR /pet follow me - pet follows you around.<br>
<br>
4.  /pet guard here - pet stays in that spot and waits for orders (will still fight a monster that attacks you, but may take a while to get to you).<br>
<br>
5.  /pet report health - Pet tells you its health and also any buffs that are upon it.<br>
<br>
6.  /pet get lost - Pet kills itself instantly.<br>
<br>
7.  /pet sit down - Pet sits down, situationally useful.<br>
<br>
8.  /pet stand up - Pet stands up.<br>
<br>
That is all i can remember and all i will use ( until i get pet hold yay ). <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#989dca><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub102.ezboard.com/bthemagicianstower.showUserPublicProfile?gid=artulyn1>Artulyn1</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/anim_1.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Conjurer</span><br>  Posts: 283<br> <font color=#333333>(1/5/03 8:36:14 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerthelibrary.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=31.topic&index=38>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://members.aol.com/armiture/eq/artulyn-tag.png WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Pet Commands</span><hr size=1> There is also the <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>/pet as you were</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> command which clears out all previous commands and is supposed to clear out it's hate list so it doesn't go running off after critters. About the only time I use it is when I accidentally hit pet attack when I have a mob that's real far away targeted. The pet will remember the command and attack it when it gets close enough, which can be really really bad as I found out as a youngun in East Commons many years ago. Way back then I didn't know about either /pet back off or /pet as you were. I was trying to kill a bear but clicked on a guard by mistake, fortunately, or so I thought, it was moving away so the pet didn't go after it and I retargeted the bear and sent in the pet after getting closer to it. However a few minutes later ...<br>
